REVIEW_TITLE: Really sweet, more coconut than almond flavor
DESCRIPTION1: I got this for my two oldest girls who are athletes and can polish off a bag of granola before I'm finished putting the tear off top in the trash.. The first thing they noted is that this granola is really sweet. They limit their sugar (I know, 12 and 13 and they don't like sugar? SMH) so they both ate small dishes and then sat it aside rather than cleaning it off like they normally would. It is crunchy without being too hard, a nice crunch without hurting their teeth. No big chunks that you have to break up before you can eat it. They felt the flavor balance was off, that it was more coconut than almond and would have liked the coconut to be toned down more.. It has all natural ingredients so my athletes like that they're eating clean, but they really wish there were less sugar in it. They've been using it as a bit of a treat, but a bag has lasted almost a week, which is unheard of in this house . . .
DESCRIPTION2: They felt the flavor balance was off, that it was more coconut than almond and would have liked the coconut to be toned down more.

REVIEW_TITLE: Nick Nolte is stellar in this touching story
DESCRIPTION1: This is a great movie that deserved a much higher rating than it got at the time of its release. Nick Nolte is at his absolute best in the part of the patriarch dealing with the onset of Alzheimers and as with most families, facing that reality is a painful journey. The story is brought to life through the eyes of Matilda, the granddaughter, who has a deep love and enduring patience for whatever hurdles her grandfather brings to the family unit. Moments of light humor, such as the grandfather accidentally setting off fireworks in the middle of a garden part, keep the movie from becoming gloomy. All the performances are very good but again, one so believes Nick Nolte's role as an aging and feeble man that they would believe that is his condition, until they remember his completely different role and award winning work in the television series Graves. If you're looking for a warm-hearted story with lovable characters and good fun, give this one a try.

REVIEW_TITLE: Mix very very well before eating. Tasty.
DESCRIPTION1: For the record I bought mine at Costco but it‚Äôs the same ‚Äúketo‚Äù mix with the macadamia nuts in it. First off, there is a lot (and I mean a lot) of oil separation straight from the store. If you‚Äôve ever bought almond butter before, probably double the separation oil in the jar. I mixed for several minutes with a knife and made sure the whole thing was mixed well. It was still way runnier than almond butter by a long shot.. Flavor... way tastier than almond butter and chunkier. I think it‚Äôs the coconut that makes the flavor better not the nuts themselves. I put mine in the fridge after the first serving. Consistency once refrigerated was a different animal. Almond butter was still slightly runny and spoonable refrigerated. Not so with this. It was more the consistency of crumbly graham cracker crust. Flavor was still the same. I actually preferred it refrigerated as texture was better and it melts in your mouth. Also being refrigerated means never having to stir it again.

What makes this product different is that the "cheese" is actually a cheesy sauce inside a pouch. After you cook the pasta, you just have to drain the water and then mix in the sauce in the same pan and it's ready!. Just remember that it's still "Mac & Cheese" and hence not necessarily something you should eat often since it's loaded with calories. Also, in the case of highly processed foods like this one, vegan does not mean healthier. Having said all that, I love this product and eat it on occasion.. One last comment would be on the price - it's very expensive compared to real Mac & Cheese and unless you are vegan, it's hard to justify the price premium.

With the warm weather the kefir separated pretty quickly, so used mason jars W/lid, shook it up and released the air (slowly) anytime I saw the separation occurring. This helps circulate the milk and keep the curd from building up on the grains. I‚Äôm working on my 4th batch... and wondering how to slow this train down. lol.

You see the tea turns red due to the hibiscus flowers accompanying the cherries which colors the tea and is a great partner to the cherries. Also wonderful notes of rosehips, and raspberry.. At its price $13.99 gets you about 22 8 oz servings (assuming 1 teaspoon = 5g) which is about ~$0.64 a cup.. The bags are resealable, and this is loose leaf tea, not in tea bags so you will need a mesh container to steep your tea in.. All in all great product!

REVIEW_TITLE: Ports NOT self healing, but good BRF jars
DESCRIPTION1: The injection port is not self healing as advertised. When puncturing the port, a small amount of rubber gets stuck in the syringe needle. This does 2 things;5 stars because....Everything is great about this except one thing; makes it very hard to press down the plunger, and also creates a tiny hole which contamination can enter.. This happens whether flame sterilizing the needle or alcohol sterilizing the needle. Now an easy workaround to this is to have a hot glue gun and just dab over the hole with a tiny dot of glue, or just a tiny peice of tape. I've also just scrunched the rubber back around the hole.. Silicon ports and better quality rubber ones don't have this problem, but these jars definitely do. If purchasing, be aware of this. That said, these jars are better quality than I've been able to do at home.

DESCRIPTION1: I've had this in my cupboard for a few months. If I'd known how good it was, I wouldn't have hesitated to try it. It says to eat within 3 days of opening, and I ate almost half a jar within 10 minutes of opening it.. Cauliflower, sunflower oil, parmesan and romano cheeses, pinenuts, salt, and pepper are the main ingredients in this pesto. There's also a little kick from the citric acid that helps to preserve it. The cauliflower takes on all the other ingredient flavors so that there's no cauliflower flavor really left.. I like to have breakfast and/or lunch of a few crackers with a nice spread on them. And this works great for that purpose. It would also be great on toast or as a mix-in with pasta or as a pizza sauce. Anywhere you would normally use pesto, this product works.

First, the cookie: true butter cookie that, even though thin, melts in your mouth; the cookies are one on top of the other with no pastry or parchment paper between. I think you know what this means: the cookies stick together! If refrigerated, the cold cookies harden and cannot be pried apart without cracking or crumbling. If left at room temperature, the chocolate may melt, making separating the cookies a messy process. Are the cookies superb? Yes! Are they worth the price? Probably. Should the packaging be improved? DESCRIPTION1: There is indeed a clumping problem when mixing with water. It's "dumping that causes clumping". This works against that bc the small amounts are dissolved before any more are tapped in. Yes, it does take longer but it beats clumping frustration. DESCRIPTION1: After BBQ'ing the pork-steaks, it is my tradition to put those pork-steaks in to a large 11x17 pan and filling the pan half full with the Wickers Marinade putting into the oven for 5 hrs @ 170 degrees. I've been doing this for over 20 yrs. This is not your typical tomato based sauce, it is Vinegar based and it has a little kick to it. It is not hot, but it does have a little spice to it. If you don't want to put the pork-steaks in the over for 5 hrs, then put the pan on the BBQ pit turn it down low and keep an eye on the pan to make sure it does not go dry, for about 30 mins to an hour and you'll get the same results. (I think better results in less time). Good Luck.

Somehow we missed that these were for Nespresso... We jail-broke them and tried brewing the coffee in a reusable pod on our Keurig though, and they were ok. I'm not sure if the brewing process in Nespresso is different than in Keurig - the coffee is ground MUCH finer, and perhaps it steeps longer, because I didn't find the taste in this coffee to be anything special. It was nowhere near as robust as the smell or description suggested.. It was fine, if a little bland, when made in my Keurig... But that's obviously not how it's intended to be brewed - so judge for yourself/from actual Nespresso reviews if you have the appropriate machine. If you find yourself, like me, the subject of an erroneous purchase though, you might want to use two capsules worth of grounds to brew each cup!

The powder does seem "finer" because it is isolate but that really doesn't matter to me or anyone else. The taste is very good. It tastes very similar to the "Extreme Milk Chocolate" Whey Concentrate they sell. Put this with some milk and it really is pretty good. With water, it tastes alright but to be fair, I have never had any protein powder with water that comes out super good. Hence why I will use Fat Free Milk just so it can have that "milkshake" taste and consistency. All in all, this is definitely my go to product and I love the taste. REVIEW_TITLE: Coffee Beans More Than a Year Old Amazon?
DESCRIPTION1: I've purchased these beans for a couple of years now. They are perfect for making Americanos in my Breville Espresso Machine. The crema is as promised: supreme! The flavor is rich without being dark.. But the last two or three month's shipments (at least) have had manufacture/packaged dates of at least 6 months old. This didn't used to be the case. The one shipped to me on August 18, 2021 was packaged in April 2020. That's too old y'all. Just plain disappointing.. I'm not going to return them because it's a small hassle and I wanted to use some of the beans in this last package to test for flavor and quality. The aroma from the release valve on front was good, so I thought I'd try. The coffee was less aromatic, less creamy, and less flavorful than usual.. I get that the older beans might be a carry over from Covid. These are imported beans...and so on. But selling premium beans more than a year old to people who can't check the packaging for themselves shouldn't be an option.
DESCRIPTION2: But the last two or three month's shipments (at least) have had manufacture/packaged dates of at least 6 months old.

REVIEW_TITLE: Great pregnancy tea! Worked for me!
DESCRIPTION1: I purchased this tea towards the end of all three of my pregnancies. The hope was that by drinking this tea it would help my labor process. I drank it in all of my pregnancies, and with my first it did cause some mild contractions but with each subsequent pregnancy that effect was lessened. I can't complain! Each of my labors were fairly quick and with each of my daughters I pushed for less and less time. The first was 15 minutes, second baby was 9 minutes, and my third baby was out with only 6 minutes of pushing! My water broke naturally with all three, ironically all of my labors were 10 1/2 hours long. The taste isn't the greatest but I'm not a big tea drinker anyways. I added sugar and honey for flavor. If I do decide to have another baby in the future I will most definitely buy this tea again.

REVIEW_TITLE: Lipton Cold Brew Is So Refreshing!
DESCRIPTION1: I've been using Lipton Cold Brew for years now. It's much easier to make since there's no brewing. I use a small amount of warm water with the sugar (I don't drink it unsweetened) & stir until the sugar is dissolved, fill the pitcher up with cold water, add the teabags & wait for about 20 minutes as I like mine stronger. Ten minutes is long enough for some people, it's just a matter of what you like best. Take out the tea bags, stir it up, put it in the fridge to chill & you have the most refreshing & great tasting tea. I haven't used brewed tea since the day I tried Lipton Cold Brew. I have tried three other brands of cold brew tea when Lipton wasn't available where I shop but I came back to Lipton before I ever finished the other brands. That's why I bought this three box pack from Amazon (3 boxes with 22 tea bags in each box). So happy to find my favorite brand here! Great price for the best tea! I highly recommend it.

After grinding the beans in my burr grinder, I used the cold brew setting on my Breville coffee maker for a 14 hour cold brew, and the result was smooth, low-acid, and complex. The roasted date is listed as being only a month ago (your mileage may vary) and the best-by date is appropriately six months later, exactly the length of time good beans should be used by. The best-by dates of brands like Starbuck's are far too much in the future.. This small roasting company from Brooklyn seems to know what it's doing. That said, Squeeze Dried's Beetroot Superfood and Nutritional Supplement in Convenient Powder Packs is a convenient way to get the healthy benefits of beets and the other ingredients. I put that into a plastic container (to hold it upright) poured 3/4 full of the quart size bag of filtered well water in, let it sit overnight outside (we had 30¬∞ temp) in the morning I poured 1/3 into an 11 ounce empty mermaid logo co. glass bottle 1/3 milk & 1/4 cup of liquid coffee creamer. It tastes awesome! Strong but not bitter & it kept me caffeinated twice as long as any of the drive thru coffee shops cold brew that I usually buy. I like that it came out dark black color, like real coffee used to look when perculated. I got 6, 11ounce Coffees ( including the creamer & milk I put in) so for me that means 24, 11 ounce coffees from their whole container the way I made It & It didn't taste watered down, it tastes nice & strong.

It also acts as a thickener, so keep that in mind when adding to casseroles, etc. I really like adding it to watery soups as it thickens it up and makes the soup a bit more hearty to eat. But note that it does give whatever you add it to a taste of "peas". Not bad at all, but it will slightly take on that aroma. So not something you want to add to your oatmeal! Overall, a great product. But I use it primarily in soups for lunch or casserole-type meals for dinner. Others mentioned that the taste seemed rancid or bad -- never had that problem. DESCRIPTION1: The front says sweetened with Splenda. Under that there‚Äôs a disclaimer about the jelly beans killing your gut. On the ingredient list on the back, the first and second ingredients listed are maltitol and maltitol syrup. Sucralose (Splenda) is one of the last ingredients listed. This is deceptive advertising. They add a trace amount of sucralose (Splenda), so they can plaster it on the front of the bag as the sweetener. In fact, maltitol is the sweetener. We love Splenda, so we blindly make the purchase. Then, we eat them and taste that bitter maltitol aftertaste. We can‚Äôt figure out the problem. Splenda has never tasted bitter. Then, we look at the ingredients and have an aha moment. Also, seven bucks for two ounces is abhorrent. If another Jelly Belly product ever touches my lips, I hope my lips fall off. Never again! I do not patronize companies that practice deception.
DESCRIPTION2: In fact, maltitol is the sweetener.

Not only is this milk delicious (I could never drink regular milk again as it has no taste) but the goats are treated humanely. I called and discussed this with the farm. My dogs love it and it is naturally low in lactose hence why babies are fed goat's milk. I tell my friends to do a "taste test" and then you choose! I also buy Certified Humane eggs (and the regulars markets carry them) and chicken. A little bit of buying products from kind treatment of animals does help.

DESCRIPTION1: For the past few winters the rabbits have been destroying my burning bush hedge row. I tried everything. I came across a blog that mentioned putting Tabasco sauce in water and spraying with that. It kind of worked, but the rabbit was willing to put up with the burning pain to some extent.. I decided it was time to get their attention. Two capfulls of the Reaper and a gallon of water in a sprayer seems to be a deterrent. Even the deer keep their distance. After a fresh snowfall I saw rabbit paw prints going to the burning bushes and then going away. Usually their droppings are in a neat pile but the droppings now looked like they had been fired out of a shotgun. Kind of gives them a gentle reminder on the way out. I spray the 11 bushes once a week just to be sure and I plan on spraying even in the warm weather just to be safe. I haven't put any Carolina Reaper on my tongue yet and don't plan too.
DESCRIPTION2: Two capfulls of the Reaper and a gallon of water in a sprayer seems to be a deterrent.

REVIEW_TITLE: Rich dark roast coffee with an interesting surprise
DESCRIPTION1: This single origin dark roast coffee from Guatemala has a deep and assertive aroma in the bag, which is another way of saying that my expectations were of a deliciously robust, rich and chocolaty coffee. We ground the beans fine for an espresso machine and the entire kitchen filled with an usually strong (and delicious) aroma of coffee. I could get addicted to the smell alone, but I digress.. The crema was medium sized in depth but flavorful and long-lasting in the cup. The coffee is full-bodied and rich, with notes of chocolate and smoky molasses. There is no bitterness and a slight but pleasing acidity. The unexpected nature of this coffee is how its flavor seems to change in the cup to a lighter, wine-like elegance over time. Its flavor appears to smooth without losing its robust qualities. The finish is long and filled with pleasant memories as the coffee disappears. I recommend this excellent dark roast for its rich flavor and its absolutely "killer" aroma.
DESCRIPTION2: I could get addicted to the smell alone, but I digress.

REVIEW_TITLE: One of the best! Slight apprehension about ingredients
DESCRIPTION1: My family loves David Rio chai after being introduced to the brand by a local coffee shop. Rather than paying $5/glass we decided to purchase it in bulk. We have tried Tiger Spice and Elephant Vanilla and so far the Tiger Spice is the proven favorite.. The chai is powdered and dissolves well in warm/hot water or milk. My tip for making iced chai is to dissolve a few teaspoons in hot water first until it becomes a concentrated liquid, then add your milk and ice. It will have a much smoother taste than trying to dissolve the powder directly into cold water or milk.. The only downside to this chai? It's high in sugar and has added ingredients which are troublesome, particularly saturated fat. Consequently I only enjoy it on rare occasions, but other members in my household drink it frequently. I would love if David Rio could produce a version that leaves out the saturated fat and some of the additives. Otherwise, it's a great treat, but a high calorie one.

This is until I tried Coffee Bros ordered via Amazon. The best brew at reasonable price point is hands down the Light Roast from Coffee Bros. I don't put any cream, sweetener or flavorings in my coffee and a purist of sorts. This coffee to ME taste more like a medium blend and seems little weak to be called a dark roast with a 8oz brew cup. I would prefer a cup of Green Mountain Dark Magic over this any day.
